Good Practice in Project Organization

When starting a new analysis, organize your work by creating a structured folder system:
üìÇ r_training

üìÇ scripts/ (code)
üìÇ data/ (datasets)
üìÅ outputs/ (results like plots, tables, etc.)







graph TD;
    A[r_training] --&gt; B[scripts];
    A --&gt; C[data];
    A --&gt; D[outputs];












Note


Use lowercase and hyphens (-) instead of spaces when naming folders, files, and objects in R to maintain consistency and ease management.

Multiple Conditions
Combine conditions using: - & for AND - | for OR - ! for NOT

# High outputs AND low inputs
panel_vat[vat_outputs &gt; 100000 & vat_inputs &lt; 50000][1:3]

   firm_id declaration_date vat_inputs vat_outputs reimbursement_date
    &lt;char&gt;           &lt;POSc&gt;      &lt;int&gt;       &lt;int&gt;             &lt;POSc&gt;
1:    &lt;NA&gt;             &lt;NA&gt;         NA          NA               &lt;NA&gt;
2:    &lt;NA&gt;             &lt;NA&gt;         NA          NA               &lt;NA&gt;
3:    &lt;NA&gt;             &lt;NA&gt;         NA          NA               &lt;NA&gt;

# Using OR
panel_vat[vat_outputs &gt; 200000 | vat_inputs &gt; 200000][1:3]

